$ Shell command: mknod
@ mknod


`mknod` creates a → Linux/device-file.

It appears that the →hardware/harddisk/partition on which mknod should create a device needs to be mounted with the `-o dev,exec` (→http://askubuntu.com/questions/522116/chroot-question[chroot question on stackoverflow]).

